## ðŸ“Œ What I Learned Today
- How to load CSV files using `pandas`
- Using `read_csv()` to import datasets
- Basic data exploration with:
  - `head()` - view first 5 rows
  - `info()` - get data types and non-null counts
  - `shape` - check rows and columns

## ðŸ’» Code
```python
import pandas as pd

# Load Titanic dataset
df = pd.read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/datasciencedojo/datasets/master/titanic.csv')

# Explore the data
print("First 5 rows:")
print(df.head())

print("\nDataset Info:")
print(df.info())

print("\nDataset Shape:", df.shape)
